    "Moreover, these matrices can guide us in understanding where the model needs The modality ablation experiments aim to assess the specific contributions of different modalities within a multimodal learning framework.In Table 3, detailing the modality ablation experiments on the MOSI dataset, we observe the performance of various modality combinations across multiple performance metrics.",
    "These metrics include binary accuracy (Has0 acc 2, Non0 acc 2), F1 scores (Has0 F1 score, Non0 F1 score), multiclass accuracy (Mult acc 5, Mult acc 7), Mean Absolute Error, correlation, and loss.",
    "The results demonstrate that combinations of multiple modalities generally yield superior performance across most metrics, particularly notable in Non0 acc 2, Non0 F1 score, and Mult acc 7.",
    "This highlights the complementary nature of each modality, enhancing the model's capability to recognize complex emotional states.Similarly, Table 4 presents the performance comparison of different modality combinations for the MOSEI dataset.In the context of the MOSEI dataset, Multi-Modal Emotion Recognition Using Tensor Decomposition Fusion and Self-Supe models integrating multiple modalities consistently surpass those relying on single modalities, particularly in metrics like Mult acc 5 and Correlation.",
    "This underscores the substantial enhancement in performance achieved through multimodal fusion.."
